==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maxilliped
<hw>Max*il"li*ped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Maxilla</ets> + L. <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>,
foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the mouth appendages of
Crustacea, situated next behind the maxillae. Crabs have three pairs,
but many of the lower Crustacea have but one pair of them. Called also
<altname>jawfoot</altname>, and <altname>foot jaw</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maxillo-mandibular</ent>⟦br⟧
